ctPicNumberEntries.name: ctPicNumberEntries
ctPicNumberEntries.description: Defines the number of PIC modules defined by this MIB.

ctPicTable.name: ctPicTable
ctPicTable.description: A table that describes the contents of all PIC modules accessible by this module.

ctPicEntry.name: ctPicEntry
ctPicEntry.description: Description of a specific instance of a PIC module.

ctPicSlot.name: ctPicSlot
ctPicSlot.description: Specific slot which the module that realizes this PIC resides. If the PIC is associated with the chassis and not a specific module then this value will be 0.

ctPicIndex.name: ctPicIndex
ctPicIndex.description: Uniquely identifies the instance of a PIC in a particular slot.

ctPicLocation.name: ctPicLocation
ctPicLocation.description: Defines location of the PIC chip. This takes on any of the encoding values defined below for backplane, module, daughter board, brim.

ctPicStatus.name: ctPicStatus
ctPicStatus.description: Provides the status of the specific PIC chip. the values are defined as follows: other(1) - firmware can not determine status present(2) - PIC seems to be functional notPresent(3) - PIC not found but expected checkSum(4) - A check sum error occured error(5) - An undefined error condition exists. limited(6) - A limited PIC implementation only type code information is present.

ctPicVersion.name: ctPicVersion
ctPicVersion.description: Reflects the version of the PIC implementation that this PIC conforms to. This has the format x.yy . If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicModuleType.name: ctPicModuleType
ctPicModuleType.description: Defines the standard module type value as defined in ctron-oids.

ctPicMfgPN.name: ctPicMfgPN
ctPicMfgPN.description: Describes the manufacturing level part number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 7 Characters Part Number 2 Characters Rework Location. If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfgSN.name: ctPicMfgSN
ctPicMfgSN.description: Describes the manufacturing level serial number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 3 bytes - Date code (year/week) 4 bytes - Serial number 2 bytes - Manufacture location 3 bytes - Board level revision If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfgPartNumb.name: ctPicMfgPartNumb
ctPicMfgPartNumb.description: This object presents the part number portion of the ctPicMfgPN object. This object contains the same information however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfgSerialNumb.name: ctPicMfgSerialNumb
ctPicMfgSerialNumb.description: This object presents the serial number portion of the ctPicMfgSN object. This object contains the same information however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfgReworkLocation.name: ctPicMfgReworkLocation
ctPicMfgReworkLocation.description: The 2 character code that defines the location this module was last reworked. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfgPN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfgMfgLocation.name: ctPicMfgMfgLocation
ctPicMfgMfgLocation.description: The two character code that defines the location this module was manufactured at. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfgSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfgDateCode.name: ctPicMfgDateCode
ctPicMfgDateCode.description: The 3 byte date code field when this module was last reworked. This is in year/week format. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfgSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfgRevisionCode.name: ctPicMfgRevisionCode
ctPicMfgRevisionCode.description: The 3 character board level revision code field of this module. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfgSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicTLPN.name: ctPicTLPN
ctPicTLPN.description: Describes the top level part number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 7 Characters Part Number 2 Characters Rework Location. If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTLSN.name: ctPicTLSN
ctPicTLSN.description: Describes the top level serial number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 3 bytes - Date code (year/week) 4 bytes - Serial number 2 bytes - Manufacture location 3 bytes - Top level revision If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTLPartNumb.name: ctPicTLPartNumb
ctPicTLPartNumb.description: This object presents the part number portion of the ctPicTLPN object. This object contains the same information however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTLSerialNumb.name: ctPicTLSerialNumb
ctPicTLSerialNumb.description: This object presents the serial number portion of the ctPicTLSN object. This object contains the same information however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTLReworkLocation.name: ctPicTLReworkLocation
ctPicTLReworkLocation.description: The 2 character code that defines the location this module was last reworked. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTLPN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTLMfgLocation.name: ctPicTLMfgLocation
ctPicTLMfgLocation.description: The two character code that defines the location this module was manufactured at. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTLSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTLDateCode.name: ctPicTLDateCode
ctPicTLDateCode.description: The 3 byte date code field when this module was last reworked. This is in year/week format. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTLSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTLRevisionCode.name: ctPicTLRevisionCode
ctPicTLRevisionCode.description: The 3 character top level revision code field of this module. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTLSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicPcbRevision.name: ctPicPcbRevision
ctPicPcbRevision.description: Defines the Cabletron revision of the art work for this module. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMacAddr.name: ctPicMacAddr
ctPicMacAddr.description: The base MAC address(ethernet format)assigned to the module. If this field is not used then it should have a value of a zero length string. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicNumbRsvdAddrs.name: ctPicNumbRsvdAddrs
ctPicNumbRsvdAddrs.description: The number of reserved MAC addresses starting at the address as defined in ctPicMacAddr. If no MAC addresses are reserved this object should have a value of 0.

ctPicBoardRevision.name: ctPicBoardRevision
ctPicBoardRevision.description: Defines the Cabletron board level revision level code for this module. If non-existent, this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicModuleTypeString.name: ctPicModuleTypeString
ctPicModuleTypeString.description: Describes the module associated with this PIC in a human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicDCDCconverterType.name: ctPicDCDCconverterType
ctPicDCDCconverterType.description: Describes the voltage of the installed DCDC Converter input and output lines. If the Module does not contain a DCDC Converter this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicDCDCconvInputPower.name: ctPicDCDCconvInputPower
ctPicDCDCconvInputPower.description: Describes the maximum allowed input power for the DCDC input line. If the Module does not contain a DCDC Converter this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicSMB1promVersion.name: ctPicSMB1promVersion
ctPicSMB1promVersion.description: Describes the current version of the SMB1 prom. If the Module does not contain an SMB1 prom this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicAtmMacAddr.name: ctPicAtmMacAddr
ctPicAtmMacAddr.description: The Atm MAC address(atm format)assigned to the chassis. If this field is not used then it should have a value of a zero length string. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicOEMVendorId.name: ctPicOEMVendorId
ctPicOEMVendorId.description: Represents the OEM vendor for a product. If the Module does not program this value this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicOEMVendorName.name: ctPicOEMVendorName
ctPicOEMVendorName.description: ASCII name of the OEM vendor for the product. If the Module does not program this value this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicMfg97SN.name: ctPicMfg97SN
ctPicMfg97SN.description: Describes the manufacturing level serial number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 4 bytes - Date code (year/week) 4 bytes - Serial number 2 bytes - Manufacture location 2 bytes - Board level revision If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfg97DateCode.name: ctPicMfg97DateCode
ctPicMfg97DateCode.description: The 4 byte date code field when this module was last reworked. This is in year/week format. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfg97SN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicMfg97RevisionCode.name: ctPicMfg97RevisionCode
ctPicMfg97RevisionCode.description: The 2 character board level revision code field of this module. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfg97SN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicTL97SN.name: ctPicTL97SN
ctPicTL97SN.description: Describes the top level serial number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 4 bytes - Date code (year/week) 4 bytes - Serial number 2 bytes - Manufacture location 2 bytes - Top level revision If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTL97DateCode.name: ctPicTL97DateCode
ctPicTL97DateCode.description: The 4 byte date code field when this module was last reworked. This is in year/week format. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTL97SN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

ctPicTL97RevisionCode.name: ctPicTL97RevisionCode
ctPicTL97RevisionCode.description: The 2 character top level revision code field of this module. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTL97SN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicOEMTLSN.name: ctPicOEMTLSN
ctPicOEMTLSN.description: Describes the top level serial number of the module as specified by the OEM for this device. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks (ascii 32).

ctPicECOTable.name: ctPicECOTable
ctPicECOTable.description: Each module that contains a PIC may have several ECOs performed on it. The ctPicECOTable reflects a history of the last 5 ECOs that have been performed on this module.

ctPicECOEntry.name: ctPicECOEntry
ctPicECOEntry.description: Describes a particular PIC ECO entry.

ctPicECOSlot.name: ctPicECOSlot
ctPicECOSlot.description: Specific slot which the module that realizes this PIC resides. If the PIC is associated with the chassis and not a specific module then this value will be 0. This refers to the same slot as identified by ctPicSlot in ctPicTable.

ctPicECOIndex.name: ctPicECOIndex
ctPicECOIndex.description: The specific PIC instance that this ECO entry pertains to. This refers to the same instance as identified by ctPicIndex in ctPicTable.

ctPicECOID.name: ctPicECOID
ctPicECOID.description: Uniquely defines the ECO entry that is being described by this conceptual row.

ctPicECONumber.name: ctPicECONumber
ctPicECONumber.description: Defines Cabletron's ECO number that describes the revision of the hardware. This object is organized as follows: 6 Characters ECO Number 2 Characters Rework Location 4 Characters Date Code

ctPicDiagTable.name: ctPicDiagTable
ctPicDiagTable.description: Each module that contains a PIC may have several Diags performed on it. The ctPicDiagTable reflects a history of the last 8 Diags that have been performed on this module. Important: This table only contains entries diagnostic entries that are defined. Therefore it is possible for this table to be empty 'does not respond to a GET or GET-NEXT' if there are no diagnostic errors present.

ctPicDiagEntry.name: ctPicDiagEntry
ctPicDiagEntry.description: Describes a particular PIC Diag entry.

ctPicDiagSlot.name: ctPicDiagSlot
ctPicDiagSlot.description: Specific slot which the module that realizes this PIC resides. If the PIC is associated with the chassis and not a specific module then this value will be 0. This refers to the same slot as identified by ctPicSlot in ctPicTable.

ctPicDiagIndex.name: ctPicDiagIndex
ctPicDiagIndex.description: The specific PIC instance that this Diag entry pertains to. This refers to the same instance as identified by ctPicIndex in ctPicTable.

ctPicDiagID.name: ctPicDiagID
ctPicDiagID.description: Uniquely defines the Diag entry that is being described by this conceptual row.

ctPicControlTable.name: ctPicControlTable
ctPicControlTable.description: A table allowing management control of PIC functionality.

ctPicControlEntry.name: ctPicControlEntry
ctPicControlEntry.description: Describes a particular PIC Control Table entry.

ctPicRefresh.name: ctPicRefresh
ctPicRefresh.description: Setting this value causes the PIC Driver to clear cached memory and to reread the PIC chip. This functionality removes the need for manufacturing to power cycle a board to ensure proper PIC programming. Reading this object always returns a zero (0).
